WEBVTT

1
00:00:15.958 --> 00:00:17.875
You have reached Jonasi Gomora.

2
00:00:17.958 --> 00:00:20.333
Please leave a message
and I'll get back to you.

3
00:00:20.416 --> 00:00:23.625
I need you to come down to the hospital.

4
00:00:24.375 --> 00:00:26.208
-Right now.
-My sister.

5
00:00:26.291 --> 00:00:28.375
I rushed here
as soon as I heard about Essie.

6
00:00:28.458 --> 00:00:30.333
Which Essie are you talking about. Magesh?

7
00:00:34.041 --> 00:00:35.958
The one you're married to?

8
00:00:37.083 --> 00:00:39.125
You can cut the act. Magesh.

9
00:00:39.916 --> 00:00:40.916
Huh?

10
00:00:42.083 --> 00:00:45.208
Sarah told me everything.

11
00:00:50.541 --> 00:00:52.500
So every time you see me

12
00:00:53.291 --> 00:00:55.583
and you call me your sister-in-law.

13
00:00:57.125 --> 00:00:59.416
it's all just been a bunch of bullshit?

14
00:01:06.291 --> 00:01:08.625
You've turned me into a fucking clown.

15
00:01:37.458 --> 00:01:40.375
You know. I thought the Matipa stuff
was bad. but this?

16
00:01:40.458 --> 00:01:42.625
Even God wouldn't forgive this.

17
00:01:42.708 --> 00:01:44.125
Let me help you with that.

18
00:01:47.875 --> 00:01:49.250
-Wow. Brother.
-Sister-in-law.

19
00:01:49.333 --> 00:01:50.666
Where did you two meet?

20
00:01:50.750 --> 00:01:52.166
-We met in Soweto.
-At Sandton Mall.

21
00:01:53.041 --> 00:01:55.125
Yeah. we first met when we were kids.

22
00:01:55.208 --> 00:01:57.000
Back then. when we were growing up…

23
00:01:57.750 --> 00:01:59.041
Joyce. my child.

24
00:02:00.416 --> 00:02:01.458
It's enough now.

25
00:02:02.750 --> 00:02:04.791
This marriage is going to kill you.

26
00:02:05.500 --> 00:02:06.541
Joyce!

27
00:02:07.625 --> 00:02:08.750
Joyce!

28
00:02:09.250 --> 00:02:11.166
Joyce. Joyce!

29
00:02:13.458 --> 00:02:14.458
Oh.

30
00:02:19.125 --> 00:02:20.250
Essie.

31
00:02:22.875 --> 00:02:26.291
The two of you have got some nerve
to just show up here.

32
00:02:26.958 --> 00:02:29.041
Sarah has done nothing wrong.

33
00:02:29.916 --> 00:02:32.708
-And you know that. She's innocent--
-Nonsense!

34
00:02:33.500 --> 00:02:35.875
Don't dare tell me that rubbish.

35
00:02:36.500 --> 00:02:37.916
Essie.

36
00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:39.833
I trusted you.

37
00:02:40.875 --> 00:02:42.875
I opened my home to you.

38
00:02:43.583 --> 00:02:47.958
You were around my children.
I came to you as a trusting sister.

39
00:02:48.041 --> 00:02:51.458
asking for advice from you
while you were doing this behind my back?

40
00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:56.458
At least now you know exactly
how we've felt after all these years.

41
00:02:56.541 --> 00:02:58.708
-Ah.
-We've kept this secret

42
00:02:58.791 --> 00:03:02.250
because we're afraid that the truth
would actually break you.

43
00:03:02.333 --> 00:03:04.333
Sarah has been dying inside.

44
00:03:04.916 --> 00:03:06.916
The 20 years that you speak of

45
00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:10.291
was 20 years that my children and I
have been living like outcasts.

46
00:03:10.375 --> 00:03:13.041
watching you guys be a happy family.

47
00:03:13.125 --> 00:03:18.541
So you. you're not supposed to cry because
you're not supposed to be heartbroken

48
00:03:18.625 --> 00:03:20.708
while some of us die from the inside

49
00:03:20.791 --> 00:03:24.583
so that you can sit on your throne
as the queen of this home.

50
00:03:25.750 --> 00:03:26.791
Fuck off.

51
00:03:27.750 --> 00:03:29.166
Is Sarah's father…

52
00:03:30.666 --> 00:03:31.875
here?

53
00:03:32.916 --> 00:03:35.625
Does he even know that I was in hospital?

54
00:03:36.958 --> 00:03:41.041
Essie. I said fuck off.

55
00:03:42.708 --> 00:03:44.708
-Fuck off. Get out of my house.
-Let's go.

56
00:03:44.791 --> 00:03:46.333
-Let's go. Sarah.
-Just go!

57
00:03:46.958 --> 00:03:49.083
You need to leave. Leave.

58
00:03:50.416 --> 00:03:51.458
Let's go. Sarah.

59
00:04:01.416 --> 00:04:05.083
Mom. I don't think it's a good idea for
you to be drinking while on medication.

60
00:04:05.166 --> 00:04:06.208
Oh.

61
00:04:06.291 --> 00:04:09.750
Sarah. I know. but it's just one drink.
Come on.

62
00:04:11.041 --> 00:04:12.875
-Wow.
-Why? Where are you off to?

63
00:04:13.416 --> 00:04:14.583
To J&J.

64
00:04:14.666 --> 00:04:15.791
-To talk to Dad.
-Really?

65
00:04:15.875 --> 00:04:19.083
Well. the truth is out now.
so we need to talk and find a way forward.

66
00:04:20.166 --> 00:04:21.958
Oh. I'll come with you.

67
00:04:22.041 --> 00:04:24.375
-Give me my crutches.
-Uh-uh. Mom. Sit down. Relax.

68
00:04:24.458 --> 00:04:25.958
I'll go talk to Dad.

69
00:04:26.750 --> 00:04:27.958
I know it's strange. Mom.

70
00:04:28.041 --> 00:04:31.750
but I have a good feeling…
…about what's about to happen.

71
00:04:31.833 --> 00:04:35.041
This is a new chapter for you and me.
For us. For our family.

72
00:04:35.125 --> 00:04:37.958
Everything I've ever wanted
will finally happen. Mom.

73
00:04:38.041 --> 00:04:39.541
So bye-bye.

74
00:04:39.625 --> 00:04:41.875
But… But we could still go together.

75
00:04:48.708 --> 00:04:51.500
-Essie is Jonasi's wife?
-Hmm.

76
00:04:51.583 --> 00:04:52.875
His second wife.

77
00:04:52.958 --> 00:04:55.791
-Where does all of this place me?
-You're number three.

78
00:04:56.375 --> 00:04:59.208
You're the third wife.
but. then again. that's if

79
00:04:59.833 --> 00:05:03.750
there aren't any more who will come
crawling out the woodworks

80
00:05:03.833 --> 00:05:05.000
to claim their place.

81
00:05:05.500 --> 00:05:07.833
You're so calm about all of this.

82
00:05:07.916 --> 00:05:09.166
How are you so relaxed?

83
00:05:09.250 --> 00:05:11.083
W-What do you want me to say?

84
00:05:11.166 --> 00:05:12.875
Be sick and cry?

85
00:05:12.958 --> 00:05:14.625
And throw a fit?

86
00:05:14.708 --> 00:05:17.875
My dear. I've been down that road.

87
00:05:17.958 --> 00:05:21.291
It's not like it changed anything
and stuff.

88
00:05:21.875 --> 00:05:23.083
I'm still here.

89
00:05:32.833 --> 00:05:33.833
Here.

90
00:05:38.583 --> 00:05:40.916
Here. Take it. Come on. now.

91
00:05:41.583 --> 00:05:44.458
You want to cry?
Rather cry because of the wine.

92
00:05:45.500 --> 00:05:47.916
There's nothing we can do.

93
00:05:49.041 --> 00:05:52.000
Let me welcome you to my pity party.

94
00:05:52.666 --> 00:05:54.416
No. wait. wait. wait.

95
00:05:54.500 --> 00:05:56.000
What are we toasting to now. Joyce?

96
00:05:56.083 --> 00:06:01.250
We're toasting to Jonasi. my sister wife.

97
00:06:03.875 --> 00:06:08.291
Oh. heavens.

98
00:06:09.708 --> 00:06:10.958
Wow. baby girl.

99
00:06:11.666 --> 00:06:13.208
You look beautiful.

100
00:06:13.291 --> 00:06:15.250
-What brings you here?
-I came to see my dad.

101
00:06:15.333 --> 00:06:17.083
'Cause everything is
out in the open now. Uncle.

102
00:06:18.458 --> 00:06:20.791
And does he know you're here to see him?

103
00:06:20.875 --> 00:06:21.958
No. he doesn't.

104
00:06:22.041 --> 00:06:24.416
But the truth is out now
and everyone knows what's going on.

105
00:06:24.500 --> 00:06:26.041
And I want us to get coffee

106
00:06:26.125 --> 00:06:28.750
and bond like father and daughter.

107
00:06:28.833 --> 00:06:31.833
Everything I wanted is coming true. Uncle.

108
00:06:34.041 --> 00:06:35.916
Hi. Sarah. How can I help you?

109
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:37.500
Um. I'm here to see my dad.

110
00:06:39.833 --> 00:06:41.541
You were just with him.

111
00:06:41.625 --> 00:06:44.875
No. no. no. my real dad. Jonasi Gomora.
Is he in?

112
00:06:45.875 --> 00:06:47.458
Uh. okay.

113
00:06:47.541 --> 00:06:50.791
Um. Mr J is out.
but he should be back in 15 minutes.

114
00:06:50.875 --> 00:06:52.833
Don't worry. I'll wait for him
in his office. Thank you.

115
00:06:52.916 --> 00:06:53.916
Okay.

116
00:06:57.708 --> 00:06:59.958
Mpume. you have a visitor.

117
00:07:00.916 --> 00:07:02.833
-Let me explain.
-What are you doing here. Bongs?

118
00:07:02.916 --> 00:07:04.333
-I want to fix things.
-Fix what?

119
00:07:04.416 --> 00:07:06.791
I didn't plan any of this.
Sarah came onto me.

120
00:07:06.875 --> 00:07:09.875
-Oh. so I'm the fool and you're right?
-That's not what I'm saying.

121
00:07:09.958 --> 00:07:11.625
How many times have you told me
you're not ready

122
00:07:11.708 --> 00:07:12.750
-and I waited for you?
-Leave.

123
00:07:12.833 --> 00:07:13.916
-I'm sorry. Wait!
-Leave. Bongs.

124
00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:15.500
-I just want to fix things.
-For what?

125
00:07:15.583 --> 00:07:17.333
I just want to fix things between us.
Mpume. please.

126
00:07:17.833 --> 00:07:19.541
-Please leave. Bongs.
-How's this your concern?

127
00:07:19.625 --> 00:07:21.833
-You know how? You've hurt my friend.
-How is this your business?

128
00:07:21.916 --> 00:07:23.208
Stop involving yourself.
What's your problem?

129
00:07:23.291 --> 00:07:24.958
I will involve myself
because you've hurt my friend.

130
00:07:25.041 --> 00:07:26.416
-Why are you involving yourself?
-Leave!

131
00:07:26.500 --> 00:07:28.375
-Hey. hey. Whoa.
-Come down with me.

132
00:07:28.458 --> 00:07:30.541
So you have the nerve to come to our house
and do this shit?

133
00:07:30.625 --> 00:07:32.666
-Please. I'm trying to speak to Mpume.
-To do what? Get out.

134
00:07:32.750 --> 00:07:33.750
-I wanna fix things.
-Get out.

135
00:07:33.833 --> 00:07:35.416
-Get out!
-I'm not trying to fight.

136
00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:38.291
Are you trying to fight? Huh?

137
00:07:38.375 --> 00:07:39.916
-What are you…
-Bongs.

138
00:07:40.458 --> 00:07:41.541
Did you just push me?

139
00:07:41.625 --> 00:07:43.208
So you wanna put your hands on me?

140
00:07:44.083 --> 00:07:45.208
Get out!

141
00:07:45.291 --> 00:07:46.750
You tell him. Menzi.

142
00:07:47.333 --> 00:07:50.458
You're full of shit.
Get out of here. Get out. Get out!

143
00:07:50.541 --> 00:07:52.500
-You're a dog.
-Oh. my word.

144
00:07:53.333 --> 00:07:54.333
I thought we were brothers.

145
00:07:54.416 --> 00:07:56.583
And you kept something like this from me?
A secret like this?

146
00:07:56.666 --> 00:07:59.625
Hey. hey. hey.
You-- You just hold it right there.

147
00:07:59.708 --> 00:08:01.541
Imagine how my mother would've felt

148
00:08:01.625 --> 00:08:04.166
knowing that I went behind her back
and betrayed her

149
00:08:04.250 --> 00:08:05.708
to people who don't even like me?

150
00:08:05.791 --> 00:08:07.791
You need to stop
acting like a little girl.

151
00:08:07.875 --> 00:08:09.791
What the hell is wrong with you? Wow.

152
00:08:09.875 --> 00:08:13.208
At least now you know the reason why
your father and I don't get along.

153
00:08:13.750 --> 00:08:15.375
It's all because of
this shit that he does.

154
00:08:15.458 --> 00:08:18.041
-Jonasi is an asshole.
-Yes. he's an asshole.

155
00:08:18.125 --> 00:08:20.041
But there's one thing I commend him for.

156
00:08:20.125 --> 00:08:22.541
Bro.

157
00:08:22.625 --> 00:08:25.125
That man doesn't play games
when it comes to sex.

158
00:08:25.208 --> 00:08:27.916
-You see now? So this is a joke to you?
-Come on. Come on. bro.

159
00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:29.541
You're making a joke out of this shit?

160
00:08:30.125 --> 00:08:31.708
Ah. piss off.

161
00:08:31.791 --> 00:08:33.750
Just give me a break.

162
00:08:35.708 --> 00:08:37.833
You're turning this into a joke.
What's so funny?

163
00:08:37.916 --> 00:08:39.000
You want to hit me with a brick?

164
00:08:39.541 --> 00:08:42.166
-You want to hit me?
-I'm not as crazy as you. Take this.

165
00:08:42.250 --> 00:08:44.541
Here. Hit me. nigga.

166
00:08:45.291 --> 00:08:48.333
-You want to hit me with a brick?
-You're the man now. right?

167
00:08:48.416 --> 00:08:49.625
Hit me then. nigga.

168
00:08:50.208 --> 00:08:52.375
I'm giving you permission. Hit me. nigga.

169
00:08:52.458 --> 00:08:55.208
I want you to release that anger.
Show me. Hit me.

170
00:08:55.291 --> 00:08:57.291
-Hey!
-You must be out of your mind.

171
00:08:57.375 --> 00:08:59.250
-You idiot! You almost hit me.
-You said I must hit you.

172
00:08:59.333 --> 00:09:01.333
What if you really hit me?

173
00:09:01.416 --> 00:09:03.333
Huh? Why are you so stupid?

174
00:09:03.416 --> 00:09:05.541
You are lucky
that I really care about you.

175
00:09:05.625 --> 00:09:07.916
Let's go. man. Get in the car. Let's go.

176
00:09:09.083 --> 00:09:11.208
-Ah. shucks.
-You've really lost your mind. huh?

177
00:09:11.291 --> 00:09:12.541
You did said I must hit you.

178
00:09:24.750 --> 00:09:26.166
Oh. hi. Dad.

179
00:09:26.875 --> 00:09:27.875
Sarah.

180
00:09:27.958 --> 00:09:30.083
I printed and framed our portrait.

181
00:09:30.666 --> 00:09:33.083
Wait. wait. wait. What're you doing here?

182
00:09:33.166 --> 00:09:36.666
Um. I brought your… your pen.

183
00:09:36.750 --> 00:09:38.583
You left it at home on your birthday.

184
00:09:38.666 --> 00:09:39.750
Here it is.

185
00:09:40.291 --> 00:09:42.458
Oh. thank you.

186
00:09:43.416 --> 00:09:48.083
I was just thinking. maybe we could
go out. grab coffee and talk?

187
00:09:48.166 --> 00:09:50.750
Oh. no. Sarah… …I actually have a meeting.

188
00:09:50.833 --> 00:09:53.208
Uh. it's actually an urgent meeting.

189
00:09:54.208 --> 00:09:56.000
I actually came to grab these files.

190
00:09:56.083 --> 00:09:59.583
Um. that's fine.
How long will your meeting take?

191
00:09:59.666 --> 00:10:02.750
Uh. it could be an hour
or maybe even two hours. Who knows?

192
00:10:02.833 --> 00:10:04.791
I'm not in a rush.
I'll sit and wait for you here.

193
00:10:04.875 --> 00:10:07.208
No. no. no. Uh…

194
00:10:07.291 --> 00:10:08.875
You don't need to do all of that.

195
00:10:10.208 --> 00:10:13.000
I mean. you can also see
it's getting late now.

196
00:10:13.083 --> 00:10:14.208
Uh…

197
00:10:14.291 --> 00:10:17.000
Listen. here's what you can do.
Go speak to Buhle

198
00:10:17.083 --> 00:10:20.208
and ask her to slot you into my diary
so I don't forget.

199
00:10:20.291 --> 00:10:21.375
Then we can do lunch.

200
00:10:21.458 --> 00:10:22.458
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

201
00:10:22.541 --> 00:10:25.333
Whoa. wait! Hey. hey.

202
00:10:35.208 --> 00:10:36.208
Wow.

203
00:10:37.083 --> 00:10:39.416
Oh. would you look at that.

204
00:10:40.333 --> 00:10:43.958
Man of the moment. You're back. Hmm?

205
00:10:45.208 --> 00:10:46.375
Wow. Jo.

206
00:10:47.375 --> 00:10:49.458
It must be nice being you.

207
00:10:49.541 --> 00:10:51.916
You just carry on like nothing happened.

208
00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:53.291
Business as usual.

209
00:10:54.541 --> 00:10:57.791
Now that you're here.
won't you please enlighten me.

210
00:10:59.375 --> 00:11:03.291
How many more bitches
are you sleeping with? Hmm?

211
00:11:03.916 --> 00:11:05.083
Do you have any more kids?

212
00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:07.541
Are there any others I can expect?

213
00:11:08.625 --> 00:11:11.791
What about wives? Are there more? Hmm?

214
00:11:11.875 --> 00:11:15.875
And I've also found out about Sarah.

215
00:11:15.958 --> 00:11:17.291
What about Freedom?

216
00:11:17.375 --> 00:11:18.458
Is he also yours?

217
00:11:18.541 --> 00:11:19.541
Wow.

218
00:11:23.916 --> 00:11:25.833
-No.
-Oh.

219
00:11:26.416 --> 00:11:29.291
Good to know that you do miss sometimes.

220
00:11:32.041 --> 00:11:33.875
Is there anything else
you'd like to confess to me?

221
00:11:34.375 --> 00:11:39.333
No. I'm just asking because
too many surprises keep popping up.

222
00:11:39.416 --> 00:11:40.583
and. honestly. I'm tired.

223
00:11:40.666 --> 00:11:46.083
So rather just tell me now.
what other sneaky things have you hidden?

224
00:11:53.500 --> 00:11:55.208
Listen. Joyce.

225
00:11:55.291 --> 00:11:56.291
Hmm?

226
00:11:57.541 --> 00:11:58.541
I'm sorry.

227
00:12:00.333 --> 00:12:01.666
I am sorry.

228
00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:05.625
Well. you listen here.

229
00:12:06.541 --> 00:12:10.958
Jonasi. these apologies of yours.

230
00:12:12.083 --> 00:12:15.083
please save them.

231
00:12:15.916 --> 00:12:17.208
Do you hear me?

232
00:12:17.291 --> 00:12:22.083
Save it for someone who actually cares
because I'm no longer involved.

233
00:12:25.625 --> 00:12:27.666
I wash my hands of you.

234
00:12:30.458 --> 00:12:33.583
The truth about Essie will come out
and hit the blogs.

235
00:12:33.666 --> 00:12:35.458
Everyone will find out about it.

236
00:12:35.541 --> 00:12:37.541
What will happen to me after that?

237
00:12:38.375 --> 00:12:39.916
Why do you care about gossip?

238
00:12:40.416 --> 00:12:41.916
You survived Matipa.

239
00:12:42.416 --> 00:12:43.416
This is nothing.

240
00:12:43.500 --> 00:12:46.166
You do understand that
this isn't just about me. right?

241
00:12:47.083 --> 00:12:49.708
-This is about all the women out there…
-Joyce Gomora.

242
00:12:49.791 --> 00:12:53.791
…who look up to me. who don't know
that the life I'm living is a lie.

243
00:12:54.791 --> 00:12:58.458
I wanted to say that my husband
has also wanted to marry another woman.

244
00:12:59.208 --> 00:13:02.083
I put my foot down. and I said no. Joyce.

245
00:13:03.208 --> 00:13:06.250
But following you has given me
a change of heart.

246
00:13:07.208 --> 00:13:08.541
I love my career.

247
00:13:09.625 --> 00:13:13.250
I've sacrificed so much for it.
but I'll stop.

248
00:13:14.500 --> 00:13:17.791
Ivory Oasis Baths. Treat yourself.

249
00:13:20.083 --> 00:13:22.625
